---
---

<section class="problem" data-test="problem-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">The Specification Problem</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">
        Sound familiar? You're not alone. These pain points plague development teams everywhere.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card" data-test="spec-drift-problem">
        <div class="problem-icon">📄➡️🗑️</div>
        <h3 class="problem-title">Specification Drift</h3>
        <p class="problem-description">
          That beautiful Google Doc becomes outdated the moment development starts.
          Developers implement features differently than specified, but no one updates
          the documentation. Six months later, your spec is fiction.
        </p>
        <ul class="problem-symptoms">
          <li>"Wait, this doesn't match the spec..."</li>
          <li>Duplicate work from miscommunication</li>
          <li>New teammates get confused by outdated docs</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card" data-test="philosophy-gap-problem">
        <div class="problem-icon">🤔💭❓</div>
        <h3 class="problem-title">Philosophy-Implementation Gaps</h3>
        <p class="problem-description">
          Your product vision sounds great in meetings, but how does "user-friendly"
          translate to actual button placement? Teams interpret abstract concepts
          differently, leading to inconsistent user experiences.
        </p>
        <ul class="problem-symptoms">
          <li>"That's not what I meant by intuitive..."</li>
          <li>Design and engineering misalignment</li>
          <li>Feature creep from unclear boundaries</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card" data-test="ai-unreliability-problem">
        <div class="problem-icon">🤖🎲💥</div>
        <h3 class="problem-title">Unreliable AI Output</h3>
        <p class="problem-description">
          AI tools promise to build your app from descriptions, but they hallucinate
          features, misunderstand context, and produce code that barely resembles
          your requirements. You spend more time fixing than building.
        </p>
        <ul class="problem-symptoms">
          <li>"This isn't even close to what I asked for..."</li>
          <li>Constant back-and-forth with AI tools</li>
          <li>Fear of losing control over your codebase</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="problem-summary">
      <h3 class="summary-title">The Root Issue</h3>
      <p class="summary-text">
        <strong>Traditional specifications don't guide implementation.</strong>
        They document what you <em>think</em> you want, not what you actually need to build.
        Without clear structure and upward references, specs become suggestions rather than blueprints.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem {
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    padding: 5rem 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .problem-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .section-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .problems-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .problem-card {
    background: var(--color-bg-primary);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-neutral-200);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
  }

  .problem-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
  }

  .problem-icon {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: block;
  }

  .problem-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .problem-description {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .problem-symptoms {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .problem-symptoms li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-error);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .problem-symptoms li::before {
    content: "→";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-error);
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .problem-summary {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-neutral-100) 0%, var(--color-neutral-50) 100%);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
  }

  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    .problem-summary {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-neutral-800) 0%, var(--color-neutral-700) 100%);
    }
  }

  [data-theme="dark"] .problem-summary {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-neutral-800) 0%, var(--color-neutral-700) 100%);
  }

  .summary-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .summary-text {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  /* Mobile responsiveness */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .problem {
      padding: 3rem 1rem;
    }

    .problem-header {
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .problems-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .problem-card {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    .problem-icon {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }

    .problem-title {
      font-size: 1.3rem;
    }

    .problem-summary {
      padding: 2rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .problem {
      padding: 2rem 0.75rem;
    }

    .problem-card {
      padding: 1.25rem;
    }

    .problem-summary {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    .summary-text {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>